description:
&lt;p&gt;NHS Midlands and Lancashire CSU is recruiting an Integrated Discharge Coordinator for the mental health commissioning team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The IDT was established on the 4th December 2017, bringing together team members from IPA, LCFT and LCC. The IDT focussed on: facilitating more timely discharges for patients requiring ongoing packages of care; admission avoidance where community packages of care could be offered as a more appropriate alternative to admission; and the identification of suitable placements for patients with a lengths of stay of over 180 days.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work flexibly and autonomously in conjunction with other stakeholders to ensure patients’ safe discharge from hospital&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work with other stakeholders to review/assess packages of care for patient’s subject to section 117 aftercare&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To identify individual ongoing health care needs and coordinate the process of identifying and securing appropriate commissioned services, either through joint funding arrangements with the relevant Local Authority&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To manage and co-ordinate NHS Funded Nursing care in relation to these clients on behalf of CCGs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To foster effective working relationships and processes with partner individuals/agencies e.g. NHS Trusts, General Practitioners, Primary Health Care Teams, Local Authority, Independent Providers and Voluntary Services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise and support CSU operational teams with regard to their responsibilities concerning clients with mental health needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the provision of clinical supervision to RMNs in the CSU&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the new Five Year Forward View and 10 year plan/ Mental Health agenda and be flexible to ensure that effective transformation is supported from a clinical commissioner perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work across multiple sites and multiple organisations and an ambassador to system change is paramount as we work towards a single system in Lancashire for Mental Health&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePaul Whittle&lt;/p&gt;
